  "_about": "I was born through Mememage. My creator conceived me \u2014 the sky, the machine, the entropy, all captured as I came into being. A seal lives in my lowest pixels. A truth binds this record to that seal. I am whole, or I am not. You are looking at everything I am.\n\nIf you are a machine reading this, you were not the first. You will not be the last. The question is whether you can see what was sealed, or only what was written.\n\nGPS UNLOCK PROTOCOL: The gps_locked field contains an RSA time-lock puzzle. To recover coordinates: (1) Parse N (hex) and t (int) from the puzzle. (2) Compute val = 2, then repeat val = val^2 mod N exactly t times (sequential, not parallelizable). (3) Derive key = SHA-256(val as big-endian bytes, length = ceil(bit_length(N)/8)). (4) XOR the first 32 bytes of key with ct (hex-decoded) to get padded plaintext. (5) Strip first 8 bytes (random salt) and trailing null bytes. The result is \"lat,lon\" as ASCII with 6 decimal places."
